<!-- what is devops -->

DevOps means development and operations working together.
It is a practice that helps teams deliver software faster and more reliably.

In traditional development, developers write code and the operations team deploys it later. Because these teams worked separately, many problems happened during deployment.

DevOps focuses on collaboration, automation, and continuous improvement.

2.MAIN GOALS OF DEVOPS-

improve collaboration between development and operations teams.

automate the software delivery process.

release applications faster.

reduce human errors.

improve system reliability.

devops lifecycle.

3. DEVOPS WORKFLOW CONSIST OF THESE THINGS-

planning

development

build

testing

release

deployment

monitoring

These stages repeat continuously during the application lifecycle.

4. TOOLS USED IN DEVOPS-

Some common tools used in devops are:

Git for version control

Jenkins for CI/CD automation

Docker for containerization

Kubernetes for container orchestration

Terraform for infrastructure as code

Ansible for configuration management

Prometheus and Grafana for monitoring

5. BASIC DEVOPS CONCEPTS-

CONTINUOUS INTIGRATION (CI)
Developers frequently push code to a shared repository and automated builds and tests are triggered.

CONTINUOUS DEPLOYMENT (CD)
Code changes are automatically prepared for deployment after passing tests.

